      "id": "2034696009310237007",
      "text": "Cinematic Video Overviews turning a research doc into something you'd actually want to watch is a genuinely different way to consume information. The gap between \"I uploaded 10 papers\" and \"here's a video that explains all of it\" is wild to think about.\n@grok How does NotebookLM's video generation compare to other AI video summary tools for dense research content — is the cinematic format actually better for retention or just more impressive to look at?",
